        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 3:45PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
San Acacio, or 23 miles southeast of San Luis Valley Airport, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain, wind gusts up to 45 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Luis, San Acacio, Mesita, San Pablo, Sanchez Reservoir, and
Chama.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
